---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Comments from '../../components/Comments.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="A Cozy Day in Bed - Yukki's Corner"
  description="Follow Yukki's peaceful day of rest and relaxation. A heartwarming story about our Shiba Inu puppy's favorite pastime - cozy naps!"
>
  <article class="blog-post">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="post-content">
        <!-- Post Header -->
        <header class="post-header">
          <nav class="breadcrumb">
            <a href="/">Home</a>
            <span class="separator">→</span>
            <a href="/stories">Stories</a>
            <span class="separator">→</span>
            <span>A Cozy Day in Bed</span>
          </nav>

          <h1>A Cozy Day in Bed</h1>

          <div class="post-meta">
            <time datetime="2025-10-08">October 8, 2025</time>
            <span class="separator">•</span>
            <span class="read-time">3 min read</span>
            <span class="separator">•</span>
            <span class="category">Daily Life</span>
          </div>
        </header>

        <!-- Featured Image -->
        <div class="featured-image">
          <img
            src="/yukki-relaxing-in-bed.webp"
            alt="Yukki relaxing comfortably in bed surrounded by favorite toys"
            width="1200"
            height="1600"
            loading="eager"
            decoding="async"
          />
          <p class="image-caption">Yukki in peak relaxation mode 🐕💤</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Post Body -->
        <div class="post-body">
          <p class="lead">
            There's something magical about watching a puppy sleep. Today, Yukki gave us
            the perfect demonstration of the art of relaxation.
          </p>

          <h2>The Perfect Morning</h2>
          <p>
            The day started like any other - full of energy and excitement. Yukki bounded
            around the backyard, chasing butterflies and investigating every interesting
            smell. We played an intense game of fetch (Yukki's favorite!), and she showed
            off her impressive Shiba agility.
          </p>

          <p>
            After about an hour of non-stop action, I noticed her energy starting to wind
            down. She gave me that look - you know the one - where her eyes get a little
            droopy and she starts to slow down.
          </p>

          <h2>Naptime Ritual</h2>
          <p>
            Yukki has a very specific naptime ritual. First, she carefully selects which
            toys will join her for the nap. Today's chosen companions were her favorite
            squeaky duck and a well-loved plush bone. She arranged them just so around
            her sleeping spot.
          </p>

          <blockquote>
            "A Shiba's naptime is not just rest - it's an art form, carefully curated
            and executed with precision."
          </blockquote>

          <p>
            Next came the circling. Around and around she went, testing different positions
            and angles. Finally, she found the perfect spot and curled up into that classic
            Shiba donut shape.
          </p>

          <h2>The Importance of Rest</h2>
          <p>
            Watching Yukki sleep so peacefully reminded me of something important: rest is
            essential. Puppies need 18-20 hours of sleep per day for proper growth and
            development. And honestly, Yukki has become a master at it.
          </p>

          <p>
            Her little paws occasionally twitched - probably dreaming about today's
            adventures in the backyard. Every so often, a tiny "woof" escaped, making
            me wonder what exciting dreams were playing in her mind.
          </p>

          <h2>Lessons from Yukki</h2>
          <p>
            If there's one thing Yukki has taught me, it's the value of taking time to
            truly relax. In our busy lives, we often forget to slow down. But here's this
            little furball, showing us that sometimes the best thing you can do is find
            your favorite cozy spot, surround yourself with things you love, and just...
            rest.
          </p>

          <p>
            As I write this, Yukki is still snoozing away, completely content in her
            little world. And you know what? I think I'll take a page from her book and
            slow down a bit myself.
          </p>

          <div class="post-footer">
            <p>
              <strong>What about you?</strong> Does your pup have special naptime rituals?
              I'd love to hear about them in the comments below! 🐾
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Tags -->
        <div class="post-tags">
          <span class="tag-label">Tags:</span>
          <a href="#" class="tag">#ShibaInu</a>
          <a href="#" class="tag">#PuppyLife</a>
          <a href="#" class="tag">#DailyAdventures</a>
          <a href="#" class="tag">#NapTime</a>
        </div>

        <!-- Navigation -->
        <nav class="post-navigation">
          <a href="/stories" class="nav-button">← Back to Stories</a>
          <a href="#" class="nav-button">Next Post →</a>
        </nav>
      </div>

      <!-- Comments Section -->
      <Comments
        repo="YOUR-GITHUB-USERNAME/YOUR-REPO-NAME"
        repoId="YOUR-REPO-ID"
        category="Comments"
        categoryId="YOUR-CATEGORY-ID"
      />
    </div>
  </article>

  <style>
    .blog-post {
      padding: var(--space-2xl) 0;
    }

    .post-content {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .breadcrumb {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: var(--space-sm);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
      font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
      color: var(--color-text-light);
    }

    .breadcrumb a {
      color: var(--color-primary);
      transition: color var(--transition-fast);
    }

    .breadcrumb a:hover {
      color: var(--color-primary-dark);
    }

    .breadcrumb .separator {
      color: var(--color-text-light);
    }

    .post-header {
      margin-bottom: var(--space-3xl);
    }

    .post-header h1 {
      font-size: var(--font-size-4xl);
      color: var(--color-primary);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
      line-height: 1.2;
    }

    .post-meta {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: var(--space-sm);
      color: var(--color-text-light);
      font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    }

    .post-meta .separator {
      color: var(--color-secondary-dark);
    }

    .category {
      background-color: var(--color-primary-light);
      color: var(--color-white);
      padding: var(--space-xs) var(--space-sm);
      border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
      font-weight: 500;
    }

    .featured-image {
      margin-bottom: var(--space-3xl);
      border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
      overflow: hidden;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
    }

    .featured-image img {
      width: 100%;
      height: auto;
      display: block;
    }

    .image-caption {
      padding: var(--space-md);
      background-color: var(--color-secondary-light);
      text-align: center;
      color: var(--color-text-light);
      font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
      font-style: italic;
      margin: 0;
    }

    .post-body {
      font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
      line-height: 1.8;
      color: var(--color-text);
    }

    .post-body .lead {
      font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
      font-weight: 500;
      color: var(--color-text);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
      padding: var(--space-lg);
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-secondary-light) 0%, var(--color-secondary) 100%);
      border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary);
      border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    }

    .post-body h2 {
      color: var(--color-accent);
      font-size: var(--font-size-2xl);
      margin-top: var(--space-3xl);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    }

    .post-body p {
      margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    }

    .post-body blockquote {
      margin: var(--space-2xl) 0;
      padding: var(--space-xl);
      background-color: var(--color-secondary-light);
      border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary);
      border-radius: var(--radius-md);
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--color-text);
    }

    .post-footer {
      margin-top: var(--space-3xl);
      padding: var(--space-xl);
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary-light) 0%, var(--color-primary) 100%);
      color: var(--color-white);
      border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
      text-align: center;
    }

    .post-footer p {
      margin: 0;
    }

    .post-tags {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      align-items: center;
      gap: var(--space-sm);
      margin-top: var(--space-3xl);
      padding-top: var(--space-xl);
      border-top: 2px solid var(--color-secondary);
    }

    .tag-label {
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--color-text);
    }

    .tag {
      background-color: var(--color-secondary);
      color: var(--color-primary);
      padding: var(--space-xs) var(--space-md);
      border-radius: var(--radius-full);
      font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
      font-weight: 500;
      transition: all var(--transition-fast);
    }

    .tag:hover {
      background-color: var(--color-primary);
      color: var(--color-white);
      transform: translateY(-2px);
    }

    .post-navigation {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      gap: var(--space-md);
      margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
      padding-top: var(--space-xl);
      border-top: 2px solid var(--color-secondary);
    }

    .nav-button {
      padding: var(--space-md) var(--space-lg);
      background-color: var(--color-secondary);
      color: var(--color-primary);
      border-radius: var(--radius-md);
      font-weight: 600;
      transition: all var(--transition-fast);
    }

    .nav-button:hover {
      background-color: var(--color-primary);
      color: var(--color-white);
      transform: translateY(-2px);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .post-header h1 {
        font-size: var(--font-size-3xl);
      }

      .post-body {
        font-size: var(--font-size-base);
      }

      .post-body .lead {
        font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
      }

      .post-navigation {
        flex-direction: column;
      }

      .nav-button {
        text-align: center;
      }
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
